{{DISPLAYTITLE:Level 63: "The Liminal Skatepark"}}{{Class Custom Image|bg-image=Level_48_image2.jpg|class=1e - Environmental|hexagon=<span class="bounce-text" style="animation-duration:5s">1e</span>|safety=Safe|security=Stable|entity=Few Non-Entity Hazards|text-color=#FFFFFF}}
'''Level 63''' is the 64<sup>th</sup> level of [[The Backrooms]].
== Description ==
{{Blurimage|file=Level_48.webp|caption=A picture of '''Level 63.'''|hovertext=Shoe racks}}'''Level 63, also known as "the liminal skate park"''' is a small modern indoor skateboard park located on a suburban street in a constant state of midnight. The skatepark is fairly small, spanning approximately 500m<sup>2</sup> in area. '''Level 63''' is well known for the presence of The Tranquility Effect, where entities will be completely docile to wanderers. '''Level 63''' is further split into three areas: The Streets, The Skatepark, and The Basement.

=== The Skatepark ===
{{Blurimage|file=Level_48_image2.jpg|caption=A picture of the main skating area in the level|hovertext=Ramp Tricks}}The interior of The Skatepark serves as the main resting area for wanderers, as it has few environmental hazards and contains a variety of food and drinks that are safe to be consumed. A wide range of fixtures can be found in the skatepark, such as ramps, handrails, boxes, chairs, benches, lockers, vending machines, and other features that give the impression of a regular indoor skatepark.

The skatepark and its obstacles themselves are made from pine wood, the railings are made of stainless steel and are routinely treated to prevent rust. In general, the quality of the skatepark is in good condition. Skating equipment can be found in lockers or at the reception table.

A reception table can be found near the entrance of the skatepark, with a singular [[Entity 9|faceling]] operating the table. Several furniture can be found near the table, such as several chairs and wardrobes. Various objects and decorations can also be found, such as flower pots, paintings and radios emitting music.

One may find a Cafe in the area, which is a [[Entity 9|Faceling]]-run cafe with only one location; inside the skatepark. This area sells a variety of foods and beverages, priding itself on being one of the only establishments to sell imitations of food brands from [[The Frontrooms]]. If a wanderer makes a commotion, they will be led away from the Cafe.

The chairs, tables, floors, walls and ceilings of the Cafe are made by light-brown pine wood, adorned with bright yellow lighting. TVs from the 90s and above can also be found attached to the walls. Although they function quite similarly to TVs in [[The Frontrooms]], the channels that they offer are known to change every so often; ranging from backrooms-related news to entertainment videos. The Cafe is decorated with other decorations, such as flower pots and paintings.

The area serves as one of the safest areas of '''Level 63''', as the area includes a variety of resources and food. Additionally, little to no hazards are present in the area, and entities are friendly to wanderers as a result of '''The Tranquility Effect'''. (See entities page for more information about The Tranquility Effect)
== <span style="font-family: Libre Baskerville, Serif;">'''The Basement'''</span> ==
{{Blurimage|file=Level 63 Basement.png|align=right|hovertext=Storage tools..|caption=An image of the basement in '''[[Level 63]]'''.}}{{Blurimage|file=Level 63 Basement 2.png|align=right|hovertext=Storage tools..|caption=A lonely room in '''[[Level 63]]'''.}}The main skatepark provides an entrance to '''The Basement.''' Usually a metal door or a stairwell concealed behind storage rooms or under ramps serves as the entry. '''The Basement''' is cramped, poorly lighted, and heavily dependent on artificial fluorescent lighting, in contrast to the spacious, open skatepark above.

'''The Basement''' is about 300–400 m². '''The Basement''' is arranged like a labyrinth of little rooms, storage spaces, and passages. The walls are mostly made of unfinished concrete, with damp areas, peeling gray paint, and occasionally exposed pipes. Because of the low ceilings, wanderers frequently have to crouch in some areas of the level.

Vending machines, lockers, boxes, and damaged or outdated skateboarding equipment are all over '''The Basement'''. Some rooms have radios playing a constant ambient music. A feeling of '''Tranquility'''  appears to be strengthened by this music, which calms wanderers in spite of their small and dismal surroundings.

=== The Streets ===
{{Blurimage|file=989898.jpeg|caption=A picture of The Streets in '''Level 63.'''|hovertext=Shoe racks}}Outside of the skatepark, '''Level 63''' is a suburban street perpetually locked at midnight. The construction and amenities match with the American Midwest, specifically in the late 2000s. When first no-clipping into the level, wanderers will be placed outside the entrance of a skatepark. This skatepark constantly produces light through its lamps, and is the only other source of natural light in the level outside of the moon, [[Phenomenon 8|stars]] and street lamps.

Other doorways of buildings in '''Level 63''' that are not connected to the convenience store are often boarded shut. These boards are usually made out of plywood, and do not take much effort to tear down. Within the other buildings, no features have been added — leaving many with only the bare minimum of appliances.

All street lamps in '''Level 63''' has bulbs which flicker periodically, leading to epilepsy and any vehicles are disabled in some way. This disabling of vehicles can be airless tires, boots attached to cars, or the removal of steering equipment. The boots cannot be removed, as they have proved heavily resistant to All damage, including firearms, blunt force and drills. All models found in '''Level 63''' reflect the types of vehicles produced and commonly used in [[The Frontrooms]]. The climate of '''Level 63''' does not veer far from warm temperatures, with the weather being cloudy.

The Streets includes various environmental hazards, such as heavy dust buildup near the buildings of The Streets, the significant levels of pollutants, such as carbon monoxide and various nitrogen oxides, and the epilepsy from the flickering street lights. Additionally, little to no resources can be found in The Streets — thus making the area unsuitable for habitation.

== <span style="font-family: Libre Baskerville, Serif;">'''Addendum'''</span> ==
<div class="titleblock"><span class="titlebox">Recovered Note:</span>{{Blurimage|file=Level 48 image2.jpg|caption=..}}I do not know what to say about this level... everything seems perfect, and I mean everything! Finally, I get to rest, after all that hardship, I got here.

As I wandered through the empty skatepark, I remembered the days in reality when I'd walk into the distance by myself, enjoying my time. The shape and appearence of this level is truly something beautiful. The wooden, glistening ramps, the shiny, metal floors and the beauty of the enviroment can't be described.

The boxes, rails, seats, lockers, and vending machines have a fresh smell of new polish. This is truly a dream coming true! Even though nobody was here, it felt so amazing to be here! The feeling of Tranquility is like a reward from god. I never want to leave this level, ever!

Near the door, there is a welcome desk with a [[Entity 9|Faceling]] sitting behind it. I tried speaking. They didn’t react. Tried waving. Still nothing. I don't feel unsafe, though. It's peaceful. Very calm. Radios all across the room play soft music. In some way, it calms me down and I love it.

I'm still in this level. I've decided to stay in The Basement as it has the most supplies. Most of the supplies in the skatepark is either gone or moldy. I still feel the sense of Tranquility. Like I said, there is nobody to bother me. No people, no dangerous entities, no payments, no taxes, nothing at all! I'm at a sense of loneliness and I love it!
</div>

== <span style="font-family: Libre Baskerville, Serif;">'''Entities'''</span> ==
The only entities present are [[Entity 9|Facelings]] and [[Entity 6|Dullers]], both of which are friendly to wanderers as an effect of '''The Tranquility Effect''', an effect that tranquilizes entities in an unknown way.

== <span style="font-family: Libre Baskerville, Serif;">'''Colonies & Outposts'''</span> ==

=== The Skaters ===
The Skaters were is a usual skating community filled with unexperienced newbies and professionals alike, they were rivals to The José Brothers. Founded in 2006, they were the first group to make residence in this level and are determined to be permanent residents. After the discovery of the lower floor, they were expanding in membership, but so as their rivals. They are friendly to wanderers, open for trading and allowing anyone to join their group. The skaters have a current member count of 23

=== The José Brothers ===
Known for their Spanish presence, The José Brothers were rivals to The Skaters. They were the only ones who were bilingual and were helpful to other wanderers who were from Spanish origins and not English. They moved around The Backrooms and tried to find a suitable level to place their colony. Soon they found this level in 2012, they made a following here and also built a rivalry with The Skaters. However, their presence on this level was cut short due to a fight caused by one of their members with The Skaters in 2024, killing half of their population reducing it from 35 to 13, which they escaped and went to Level 610 via a secret path.

== <span style="font-family: Libre Baskerville, Serif;">'''Entrances & Exits'''</span> ==

=== <span style="font-family: Libre Baskerville, Serif;">'''Entrances'''</span> ===

* Entering a door labeled as “63” in [[Level 21]] leads here;
* Noclipping on a skateboard in [[Level 29]] will send one here;
* Wandering far enough in [[Level 38]] or [[Level 49]] leads to The Streets of the level;
* Finding a NO ENTRY door and entering it in [[Level 62]] leads here;
* A karma rating of 21 to 49 in [[Level 995]] leads here.
=== <span style="font-family: Libre Baskerville, Serif;">'''Exits'''</span> ===

* Jumping on a manhole in the Streets leads to [[Level 64]];
* There is a 20% chance that tripping on an electrical wire will cause one to fall toward the ground, leading to [[Level 66]].
* In the skatepark, there are three slides next to each other. A red slide will lead one to [[Level !]], a yellow slide will lead one to [[Level 521]] and a green slide will lead one to [[Level 833]]. The exits from the slides are subjected to change randomly.
* Causing a severe commotion in The Skatepark will prompt the [[Entity 9|Facelings]] to send one to [[Level !]] via an elevator.
* A bus stop may be found in The Streets. Approaching it will transition the level into [[Level 179]].
